        "timestamp": "2018-02-14 20:59:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nThe changes here don't line up with the JIRA ticket.  The JIRA is tracking the pending state error which you solve nicely.  What role does making the timeout configurable play?  What is your opinion on simply removing the timeout altogether?  The situation described in the jira ticket would mean that the readiness initcontainer would never fail and just loop forever at which point the user would investigate why it isn't completing leading to the pod status bug fix.",
        "patchset_number": 3
